t\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19424:\"\n<p>Are you looking for a caching plugin that minimizes load time and improves the performance of your WordPress website?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The WordPress repository offers a multitude of caching plugins, which can make it overwhelming to choose the right one. To simplify your decision, we have curated a list of the best plugins for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we have listed the best free WordPress Caching plugins that speed up your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><h2>Table of Contents</h2><nav><ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-caching-and-why-is-it-important\">What is Caching and why is it important ?</a></li><li><a href=\"#best-free-word-press-caching-plugins\">Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins</a><ul><li><a href=\"#1-lite-speed\">1. LiteSpeed</a></li><li><a href=\"#2-w-3-total-cache\">2. W3 Total Cache</a></li><li><a href=\"#3-speed-optimizer-the-all-in-one-performance-boosting-plugin\">3. Speed Optimizer &#8211; The All-In-One Performance Boosting Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#4-wp-optimize\">4. WP-Optimize</a></li><li><a href=\"#5-wp-fastest-cache\">5. WP Fastest Cache</a></li><li><a href=\"#6-cache-enabler\">6. Cache Enabler</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion</a></li></ul></nav></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-caching-and-why-is-it-important\">What is Caching and why is it important ?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When a user visits your WordPress site, a series of operations are performed to dynamically generate the content. This process includes fetching data from the database, processing server-side scripts, and rendering the final HTML output. These steps can be resource-intensive and time-consuming, particularly for high-traffic websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Caching involves storing copies of frequently requested data in a temporary storage area known as a cache. This allows the server to quickly access and deliver the data to the user upon request, significantly reducing the waiting time for the user.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some benefits of using Caching:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Caching reduces load times by serving static content, enhancing user experience.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It decreases the server’s workload, allowing it to handle more traffic.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Faster websites rank higher in search results.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Quick-loading sites increase user satisfaction and engagement.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Efficient caching can lower hosting expenses.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Caching helps manage traffic spikes effectively.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Faster sites improve user engagement and conversion rates.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A fast site enhances your brand’s credibility.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"best-free-word-press-caching-plugins\">Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"1-lite-speed\">1. LiteSpeed</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/LiteSpeed-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"LiteSpeed - Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins\n\" class=\"wp-image-11359\" title=\"Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website 38\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/LiteSpeed-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/LiteSpeed-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/LiteSpeed-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/LiteSpeed-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/LiteSpeed-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>LiteSpeed Cache for WordPress (LSCWP) is one of the best free WordPress caching plugins designed to enhance the performance of WordPress sites. It offers a powerful server-level cache and a range of optimization features to ensure faster load times and improved user experience. LiteSpeed Cache for WordPress (LSCWP) is compatible with LiteSpeed, Apache, and NGINX web servers. It supports WordPress Multisite and integrates seamlessly with popular plugins like WooCommerce, bbPress, and Yoast SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Accelerate content delivery with the free QUIC.cloud CDN, enhancing site speed globally.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Optimize images using lossless or lossy methods to reduce load times without compromising quality.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reduce file sizes and speed loading by minifying and combining CSS and JavaScript files.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improve page load times by deferring the loading of images and iframes until needed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatically cache pages to significantly boost site performance and reduce server load.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keep your database clean and optimized for better performance and faster queries.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Provide a separate cache for logged-in users, ensuring personalized content is delivered quickly.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/litespeed-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"2-w-3-total-cache\">2. W3 Total Cache</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"772\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/W3-Total-Cache-1.jpg\" alt=\"W3 Total Cache - Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins\" class=\"wp-image-11360\" title=\"Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website 39\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/W3-Total-Cache-1.jpg 772w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/W3-Total-Cache-1-300x97.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/W3-Total-Cache-1-768x249.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>W3 Total Cache (W3TC) is a powerful plugin for improving your WordPress site&#8217;s speed and performance. W3 Total Cache (W3TC) enhances SEO, Core Web Vitals, and user experience by optimizing your website&#8217;s loading speed and performance. By leveraging features like content delivery network (CDN) integration and best practices, W3TC significantly increases website performance and reduces load times. Trusted by millions of publishers, web developers, and web hosts for over a decade, W3TC is one of the best free WordPress caching plugins for optimizing WordPress websites, regardless of your hosting environment.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transparent management of Media Library, theme files, and WordPress assets.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It provides caching for mobile pages, including Accelerated Mobile Pages (AMP) and theme switching based on user agents.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ensures compatibility with secure socket layer (SSL) encryption for encrypted websites.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Caching of pages, posts, CSS, JavaScript, feeds, search results, database objects, and fragments in memory, on disk, or via CDN.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Defer non-critical CSS and JavaScript, and lazy-load offscreen images.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Implement cache control, future expire headers, and ETags for efficient browser caching.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Optimize images and use various CDN providers for enhanced performance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Command-line support for cache purging and query string updates.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Includes features to improve website security.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Provides caching statistics for performance monitoring.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"3-speed-optimizer-the-all-in-one-performance-boosting-plugin\">3. Speed Optimizer &#8211; The All-In-One Performance Boosting Plugin</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SpeedOptimizer-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"Speed Optimizer - Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins\" class=\"wp-image-11361\" title=\"Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website 40\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SpeedOptimizer-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SpeedOptimizer-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SpeedOptimizer-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SpeedOptimizer-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/SpeedOptimizer-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Speed Optimizer is one of the best free WordPress caching plugins designed to enhance user experience, increase conversion rates, and drive more traffic. It is user-friendly, enabling users of all skill levels to perform complex speed optimizations with just a few clicks. By using the Speed Optimizer plugin, you can achieve better SEO rankings, improve Core Web Vitals, and enhance your Google Page Speed Score.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Boosts website performance by up to 20%.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Minifies JavaScript, HTML, and CSS for faster loading.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It compresses images by up to 85% without quality loss.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It improves the efficiency of the website&#8217;s resources.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It provides on-demand optimization tips.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It caches non-static resources and stores static HTML versions for faster page loading.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It includes Memcached for fast database queries, cache clearing, browser-specific caching, and exclusions for specific post types and URLs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It enables HTTPS, schedules database maintenance, and controls WP Heartbeat frequency for improved performance and security.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It compresses images, uses WebP format, enables Lazy Load, and automatically resizes large images for faster loading.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/sg-cachepress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"4-wp-optimize\">4. WP-Optimize</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPOptimize-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"WP-Optimize - Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins\" class=\"wp-image-11362\" title=\"Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website 41\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPOptimize-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPOptimize-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPOptimize-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPOptimize-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPOptimize-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WP-Optimize is one of the best free WordPress caching plugins, trusted and used by over 1 million WordPress website owners to boost site speed and improve user experience. This all-in-one solution enhances your site&#8217;s performance and search engine rankings through four key features: caching, image compression, database cleaning, and minification. By leveraging WP-Optimize, you can significantly reduce page load times, improve Core Web Vitals, and ensure your website runs efficiently.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>One-click activation for automatic optimization.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cache preloading for instant page load times.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>GZIP compression to reduce page sizes by up to 90%.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lossy and lossless compression are used to achieve the best possible image quality.&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Convert to WebP for smaller file sizes.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatically compress new uploads, and bulk compress existing images.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Restore original images if needed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Removes unnecessary data like revisions and spam.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Scheduled clean-ups for automated maintenance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Backup before clean-up with UpdraftPlus.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Enable one-click minification for HTML, JavaScript, and CSS.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Customizable minification settings.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Asynchronous loading of non-critical files.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Exclude specific files from minification.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Optimize and preload fonts and other assets.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Preload the requests for improved speed times.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-optimize/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"5-wp-fastest-cache\">5. WP Fastest Cache</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"772\" height=\"251\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPfastestCache-1.jpg\" alt=\"WP Fastest Cache - Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins\" class=\"wp-image-11363\" title=\"Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website 42\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPfastestCache-1.jpg 772w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPfastestCache-1-300x98.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/WPfastestCache-1-768x250.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WP Fastest Cache plugin is one of the WordPress caching plugins designed to optimize your website performance. WP Fastest Cache is one of the best free WordPress caching plugins for speeding up WordPress sites. It enhances your site performance by improving Google PageSpeed, Core Web Vitals, GTmetrix, and Pingdom scores. By leveraging advanced caching techniques, WP Fastest Cache helps reduce page load times and factor in Google search algorithm, ultimately boosting your SEO rankings. WP Fastest Cache is user-friendly and efficient, offering comprehensive features for smooth website operation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It utilizes the Mod_Rewrite as the fastest caching method.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>When a post or page is published, it deletes all cache files.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Options to delete all cached and minified CSS/JS files.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Allows blocking cache for specific pages or posts.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatically clears cached files at set intervals.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It enables or disables caching for mobile devices and logged-in users.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It is compatible with SSL and CDN providers like Bunny CDN and Cloudflare.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatically creates a site-wide cache and allows the exclusion of specific pages and user agents.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Supports WP-CLI for command-line cache clearing and integrates with Varnish Cache for proxy cache clearing.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reduces file sizes by removing unnecessary characters, compressing files, and combining multiple files to decrease HTTP requests.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Caches resources for repeat visitors to reduce page load times and removes unnecessary emoji-related files.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-fastest-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"6-cache-enabler\">6. Cache Enabler</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CacheEnabler-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"Cache Enabler - Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins\" class=\"wp-image-11364\" title=\"Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website 43\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CacheEnabler-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CacheEnabler-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CacheEnabler-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CacheEnabler-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/CacheEnabler-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Cache Enabler is a simple yet powerful WordPress caching plugin that speeds up your site by creating static HTML files for your pages. These static files are stored on the server and delivered to visitors quickly, avoiding the slow backend processes usually needed by WordPress. It is one of the best free WordPress caching plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It creates and serves static HTML files for faster page loading.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reduces server load and improves overall site speed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The Smart cache clearing ensures that updated content is delivered promptly.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Manual cache-clearing options are available for specific needs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Command-line interface for managing cache clearing efficiently.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Set expiration times for cached files to ensure freshness.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It converts images to WebP format for optimized loading times (via the Optimus plugin).</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It ensures cached files are optimized for mobile devices.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pre-compresses files for faster delivery and reduced bandwidth usage.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Minifies HTML, optionally including/excluding inline CSS and JavaScript for further performance gains.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Monitor cache usage directly from the WordPress dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Supports caching for custom post types to improve performance across all content types.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Enhances efficiency by delivering cached content with HTTP status code 304 when unchanged.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cache-enabler/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"conclusion\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you find the best free WordPress caching plugins for your website. Choose a plugin from our curated list that is compatible with your server and meets your preferences to optimize your site, enhancing both SEO and user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found this article interesting, you might also enjoy our other articles:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/must-have-wordpress-plugins/\">Must Have WordPress Plugins</a> </li>\n\n\n\n<li> <a href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/\">Tips to Improve WordPress Security</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have any queries, please let us know in the comment section below. And thank you for reading till the end.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-wordpress-caching-plugins/\">Top 5+ Best Free WordPress Caching Plugins to Speed Up Your Website</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-wordpress-caching-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-elementor-addons-for-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-elementor-addons-for-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 28 Jun 2024 11:19:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"WordPress plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"elementor\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/?p=11325\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:355:\"<p>Are you searching for Elementor Addons for your WordPress website? Do you want to extend...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-elementor-addons-for-wordpress/\">8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Themebeez Author\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25422:\"\n<p>Are you searching for Elementor Addons for your WordPress website? Do you want to extend the functionality and features of the Elementor? If yes, then you are looking at the right place.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Elementor is a popular drag-and-drop page builder plugin for WordPress. It allows users to create custom website layouts and provides design flexibility without writing a single line of code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, to make it easy to choose Elementor addons from the wide range of options available, we have listed some of the best free Elementor addons for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><h2>Table of Contents</h2><nav><ul><li><a href=\"#what-are-elementor-addons\">What are Elementor addons?</a></li><li><a href=\"#best-free-elementor-addons-for-word-press\">Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress</a><ul><li><a href=\"#1-essential-addons-for-elementor\">1. Essential Addons For Elementor</a></li><li><a href=\"#2-elementor-header-footer-builder\">2. Elementor Header &amp; Footer Builder</a></li><li><a href=\"#3\">3. Wbcom Essential Elementor</a></li><li><a href=\"#3-elements-kit-elementor-addons\">4. ElementsKit Elementor Addons</a></li><li><a href=\"#4-premium-addons-for-elementor\">5. Premium Addons for Elementor</a></li><li><a href=\"#5-happy-addons-for-elementor\">6. Happy Addons for Elementor</a></li><li><a href=\"#6-prime-slider\">7. Prime Slider</a></li><li><a href=\"#7-met-form\">8. MetForm</a></li><li><a href=\"#8-skyboot-custom-icons-for-elementor\">9. Skyboot Custom Icons for Elementor</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion</a></li></ul></nav></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-are-elementor-addons\">What are Elementor addons?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Elementor Addons are plugins or extensions that enhance the functionality of the Elementor page builder, a widely-used WordPress plugin for creating custom website designs using a visual, drag-and-drop interface. These addons provide widgets, templates, features, and design options not included in the core Elementor plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below are some common features of Elementor Addons:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Widgets:</strong> Addons often include new widgets that you can use in your Elementor designs, such as advanced forms, sliders, pricing tables, countdown timers, and more.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>&nbsp;Pre-made Templates:</strong> Many addons come with various pre-designed templates and blocks that can be easily imported and customized to speed up the design process.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>&nbsp;Enhanced Features:</strong> Addons can provide advanced features such as animations, custom post types, dynamic content integration, WooCommerce compatibility, and enhanced responsive design options.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Styling and Design Options</strong>: Addons offer more styling and customization options, allowing users to create more unique and visually appealing designs.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Performance Optimization:</strong> Some addons include tools to help optimize the performance of your Elementor designs, ensuring fast load times and better user experience.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"best-free-elementor-addons-for-word-press\"><strong>Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"1-essential-addons-for-elementor\">1. <strong>Essential Addons For Elementor</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/EssentialAddons-2-1024x332.gif\" alt=\"Essential Addons - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\n\" class=\"wp-image-11327\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 44\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/EssentialAddons-2-1024x332.gif 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/EssentialAddons-2-300x97.gif 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/EssentialAddons-2-768x249.gif 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/EssentialAddons-2-1536x497.gif 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Essential Addons is a highly-rated, one of the best free Elementor addons that provides over 90 creative elements and extensions to enhance your WordPress pages and posts. It includes 5,000+ ready-to-use templates, advanced customization options, and WooCommerce integration. With user-friendly and requiring no coding skills, Essential Addons gives you full control over customization. It’s one of the most popular addons with higher active installations, making it a top choice for many users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Display blog posts, timelines, animated texts, and more.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrate with Contact Form 7, Gravity Forms, Ninja Forms, etc.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Access and customize 5,000+ templates.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully responsive and easy to personalize.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>They are designed for fast performance with real-time editing.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Turn widgets on or off to boost load speed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It provides you the control to deactivate unneeded widgets.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Extensive options for endless design possibilities.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>11+ Widgets for WooCommerce product displays and filters.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WooCommerce features like Product Carousel and Slider.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add progress bars, duplicate pages, custom JS, and a scroll-to-top button.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/essential-addons-for-elementor-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"2-elementor-header-footer-builder\">2. Elementor Header &amp; Footer Builder</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HeaderFooter-1-1024x332.jpg\" alt=\"Elementor Header &amp; Footer Builder - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11330\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 45\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HeaderFooter-1-1024x332.jpg 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HeaderFooter-1-300x97.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HeaderFooter-1-768x249.jpg 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HeaderFooter-1-1536x497.jpg 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HeaderFooter-1.jpg 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Elementor Header &amp; Footer Builder is the best free Elementor addons to create header, and footer in your website using Elementor. Using Elementor Header &amp; Footer Builder, you can design and create stunning headers, and footers for your website. It provides nine inbuilt widgets to create header and footer layouts. It is easy to use, and no coding skills are required.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Design beautiful headers and footers using Elementor&#8217;s flexible editor.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Display custom header and footer templates on specific pages, such as the homepage or blog archive, or across the entire site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use the shortcode to place custom Elementor templates anywhere on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add a custom template above the main footer for enhanced design flexibility.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Display your custom header/footer layouts using the Elementor Canvas Template.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Utilize built-in widgets to add header and footer elements.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compatible with all themes.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/header-footer-elementor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"3\">3. Wbcom Essential Elementor</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"780\" height=\"350\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Wbcom-1.png\" alt=\"Wbcom Essential Elementor - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11629\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 46\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Wbcom-1.png 780w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Wbcom-1-300x135.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Wbcom-1-768x345.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Wbcom Essential plugin is equipped with numerous powerful widgets, offering advanced design customizations without the need for coding knowledge. These widgets allow you to fine-tune your website for precise results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li> A widget that enables you to place the website header bar anywhere on the page, not limited to just the top.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A widget displaying member profile completion progress, showing field names and completion data.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The Member List widget, allows you to display a list of website members with Latest, Active, and Popular filters.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A carousel widget that showcases members, staff, or employees interactively on your Elementor page.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A branding widget that customizes the site title and logo, giving you control over how they are displayed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A carousel widget for WordPress posts, offering two layouts and various animation options.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A Dropdown Button widget for creating custom buttons with drop-down menus.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A Tabs widget to organize your content into multiple tab structures for easy navigation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wbcomdesigns.com/downloads/wbcom-essential/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"3-elements-kit-elementor-addons\">4. ElementsKit Elementor Addons</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ElementsKit-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"ElementsKit - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11331\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 47\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ElementsKit-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ElementsKit-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ElementsKit-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ElementsKit-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ElementsKit-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>ElementsKit Elementor Addons is an all-in-one solution for enhancing the Elementor Page Builder. It includes over 90 custom widgets and 18+ modules, making it easy to create any website. With pre-designed templates, WooCommerce integration, and fully responsive design, ElementsKit simplifies and enhances your web-building experience. It is one of the best free Elementor addons for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>50+ Free Widgets to easily add and customize elements like social icons, blog posts, client logos, and testimonials.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lightweight and easy to use.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More than 18 exclusive modules that enhance functionality with advanced options.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ready-made designs to quickly set up headers and footers.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It provides a vast library of pre-designed pages and section blocks.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrates with WooCommerce and adds product displays, cart features, etc.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Device responsiveness.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/elementskit-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"4-premium-addons-for-elementor\">5. Premium Addons for Elementor</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PremiumAddons-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"Premium Addons - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11332\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 48\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PremiumAddons-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PremiumAddons-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PremiumAddons-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PremiumAddons-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PremiumAddons-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Premium Addons for Elementor is a must-have plugin for enhancing and extending the Elementor Page Builder. It offers 90+ customizable widgets and over 550 templates, allowing you to create stunning websites without coding. It has a generous library of creative and flexible widgets, beautiful layouts, and transition effects widgets like Modal Box, Banners, Carousel, Fancy Text, Dual Heading, Image Grid, Image Scroll, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It offers over 90 widgets for various functionalities.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It provides more than 550 templates for quick website setup.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It includes an AJAX Search Form for enhanced search functionality.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The global Tooltips feature allows you to add tooltips with icons or images.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It ensures responsive design and compatibility across different browsers.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Modular and lightweight design allows enabling/disabling specific elements.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully compatible with WPML for building multilingual websites.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It enhances Elementor with features like Lottie Animations and background transitions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/premium-addons-for-elementor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"5-happy-addons-for-elementor\">6. Happy Addons for Elementor</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HappyAddons-1-1024x332.jpg\" alt=\"Happy Addons - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11333\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 49\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HappyAddons-1-1024x332.jpg 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HappyAddons-1-300x97.jpg 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HappyAddons-1-768x249.jpg 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HappyAddons-1-1536x497.jpg 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/HappyAddons-1.jpg 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Happy Addons for Elementor is a powerful, design-focused plugin that enhances your Elementor experience. With over 143 widgets, including 66 free ones, plus 70+ full-page templates and 500+ template blocks, it offers exceptional flexibility and creativity. Unique widgets like Gradient Heading, Skill Bars, and Step Flow let you create interactive, advanced designs without coding. It also supports popular tools like Mailchimp, Calendly, and WPForms, and allows you to design custom headers, footers, and templates, making your website more dynamic and visually appealing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It offers access to 143+ widgets, including 66 unique free widgets like reviews, flip boxes, and comparison tables.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>70+ full-page Elementor templates and 500+ template blocks for quick and easy design.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Employ distinctive widgets such as Gradient Heading, Skill Bars, and Step Flow to make your content more dynamic and interactive.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integration compatibility with well-known plugins like Mailchimp, Calendly, and WPForms for enhanced functionality.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Build custom headers and footers with the comprehensive Theme Builder.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Utilize advanced customization options, including setting equal heights for columns and sections, and adding background overlays.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add 18+ new shape dividers within Elementor to enhance your design.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rearrange column order on mobile devices and control column width with pixel parameters for better mobile responsiveness.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easily duplicate posts, pages, and templates with the Happy Clone feature for efficient workflow management.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/happy-elementor-addons/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"6-prime-slider\">7. Prime Slider</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"330\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PrimeSlider-1-1024x330.png\" alt=\"Prime Slider - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11334\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 50\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PrimeSlider-1-1024x330.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PrimeSlider-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PrimeSlider-1-768x248.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PrimeSlider-1-1536x495.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/PrimeSlider-1.png 1550w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Prime Slider is a Elementor addon for creating sliders for any websites build with WordPress and Elementor. It is one of the best free Elementor addons, offering over 30 modern slider designs that you can easily customize to enhance your site&#8217;s appearance. Prime Slider helps you create attractive slides with stylish features like social share buttons, customizable titles, and backgrounds. Prime Slider is the perfect plugin for quickly and easily adding stylish slides to your website for content or products.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Compatible with any WordPress theme and Elementor Page Builder.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It creates eye-catching sliders.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully responsive across all devices.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SEO optimized.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Regularly updated to ensure continue compatibility and performance enhancements.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Customization template skins.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Widgets for third-party plugins, WooCommerce, Woocircle, and Woolamp.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>RTL ready.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Translation ready.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Allows live copy/paste and duplicator.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/bdthemes-prime-slider-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"7-met-form\">8. MetForm</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/MetForm-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"MetForm - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11335\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 51\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/MetForm-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/MetForm-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/MetForm-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/MetForm-1-1536x497.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/MetForm-1.png 1544w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>MetForm stands as the ultimate drag-and-drop contact form builder for WordPress. It integrates with Elementor to deliver an easy-to-use form-building experience. MetForm is another of the best free Elementor addons providing more than 40 Elementor widget fields to facilitate the creation of various forms. This plugin allows users to create professional and customizable website forms, enhancing functionality and aesthetics.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Elementor&#8217;s drag-and-drop interface makes form building easy.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Users can upload files directly through forms.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It exports form submissions to CSV for further analysis.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Device responsiveness.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Collect and manage leads with MailChimp integration.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Save and manage form submission data within the WordPress admin panel.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Embed forms anywhere on your site using simple shortcodes.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Customization options.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/metform/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"8-skyboot-custom-icons-for-elementor\">9. Skyboot Custom Icons for Elementor</h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Skyboot-1-1024x332.png\" alt=\"Skybot Custom Icons - Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-11336\" title=\"8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024 52\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Skyboot-1-1024x332.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Skyboot-1-300x97.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Skyboot-1-768x249.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Skyboot-1-1536x498.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Skyboot-1.png 1540w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Skyboot Custom Icons for Elementor is a plugin that expands Elementor&#8217;s icon library with over 14,055 custom icons. Whether you&#8217;re looking to spice up your website&#8217;s design or enhance functionality, this plugin offers a wide range of icons like social media, UI, and specialized icons like Google and YouTube. It is one of the best free Elementor addons and ideal for users looking to personalize their site with unique and diverse icon options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It extends Elementor&#8217;s icon library with over 14,055 custom icons.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easily manage icon packs with individual ON/OFF switches.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It includes 15 different icon font packs like brands, devices, and elegant icons.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>User-friendly interface for simple icon management.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Place icons freely anywhere on your website.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It ensures fast loading times for optimized performance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It offers popular social media icons such as Facebook and Instagram.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It enhances Elementor&#8217;s default icon library with more options.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Customize icon size and color directly in the Elementor editor.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It provides icons for websites, maps, cameras, UI elements, and more.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Icons are responsive and adapt well across different devices.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"button-block\">\n<a class=\"btn-general\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/skyboot-custom-icons-for-elementor/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download</a>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"conclusion\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped you find the Best Free Elementor addons for your WordPress website. You can always use multiple Elementor Addons to meet your website requirements.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are looking for best free Elementor WordPress themes for your WordPress website, then check out our article on <a href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-elementor-wordpress-themes/\">Best Free Elementor WordPress Themes</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;ve used any of the mentioned Elementor Addons, please share your experiences in the comments below.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you for reading till the end!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-elementor-addons-for-wordpress/\">8+ Best Free Elementor Addons for WordPress in 2024</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-free-elementor-addons-for-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 21 Jun 2024 11:48:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WordPress Tutorial\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/?p=11236\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:373:\"<p>The success of any website depends upon reaching out to the right audience and visitors....</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-wordpress/\">How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Themebeez Author\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22121:\"\n<p>The success of any website depends upon reaching out to the right audience and visitors. If you are wondering how it is possible, consider providing the content your visitors want. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding Google Analytics helps to know who visited your site and what they are doing and looking for, and you can make data-driven decisions, providing them with the most suitable content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this blog post, we’ll guide you on how to add Google Analytics to your WordPress site easily. </p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><h2>Table of Contents</h2><nav><ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-google-analytics\">What is Google Analytics?</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-does-google-analytics-work\">How does Google Analytics work?</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-is-google-analytics-important\">Why is Google Analytics important?</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-to-add-google-analytics-to-word-press\">How to add Google Analytics to WordPress?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#1-set-up-google-analytics-account\">1. Set up Google Analytics account</a></li><li><a href=\"#2-add-google-analytics-to-word-press-website\">2.  Add Google Analytics to WordPress Website</a></li><li><a href=\"#3-verify-the-installation\">3. Verify the Installation</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion</a></li></ul></nav></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-google-analytics\">What is Google Analytics?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Analytics tracks website visitors, showing who visited, what they did, and how they found the site. It&#8217;s a powerful tool for understanding user interactions on websites and apps, helping businesses and site owners gain insights into user behavior, track conversions, and enhance the overall user experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"how-does-google-analytics-work\">How does Google Analytics work?</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Data Collection</strong>: Using tracking code, Google Analytics gathers data, such as page views, user interactions, session duration, and referral sources, and sends it to Google servers.  It can also collect information related to the browser settings, such as the browser used, the device, the language setting, and the operating system. Moreover, it can also track additional information like traffic sources on how they reach your site and the e-commerce transactions if set up correctly.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Data Processing:</strong> After gathering the data, Google Analytics processes it to generate meaningful reports and insights. It involves combining the data, applying filters, and calculating various metrics. Once processed, the data is stored in a database,  where data cannot be altered.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Reporting</strong>: Users can view the processed data through the Google Analytics interface. The interface provides a range of reports, dashboards, and data visualization tools to aid in interpreting the information. Users can customize reports and create personalized dashboards. Additionally, Google Analytics integrates with other platforms and tools, including Google Ads, Google Search Console, and third-party applications, to enhance data analysis and marketing efforts.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"why-is-google-analytics-important\">Why is Google Analytics important?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Google Analytics is essential for several reasons, especially for businesses, website owners, bloggers, and digital marketers. It provides comprehensive insights into website traffic, user behavior, and marketing effectiveness. Tracking key performance indicators,&nbsp; such as page views, bounce rates, and conversion rates, enables data-driven decision-making and optimization of marketing strategies. Additionally, its ability to integrate with other tools, offer real-time data, and provide custom reporting makes it an invaluable resource for improving user experience, measuring campaign success, and driving business growth—all at no cost.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>User Interaction: Google Analytics shows which pages users visit, how long they stay, and what actions they take.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Traffic Sources: It reveals where visitors come from, like search engines, social media, or referral links, helping you see which marketing works best.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Audience Segmentation: You can categorize your audience by demographics, interests, location, and device type for targeted marketing and personalized experiences.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Conversion Tracking: It tracks form submissions, purchases, and sign-ups, helping you measure campaign success.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Website Performance: Google Analytics provides data on site speed and bounce rates, helping you fix issues to improve user experience.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Marketing Optimization: Understanding user behavior and traffic sources helps you improve marketing strategies and make better decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"how-to-add-google-analytics-to-word-press\">How to add Google Analytics to WordPress?</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"1-set-up-google-analytics-account\">1. <strong>Set up Google Analytics account</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Sign Up</strong>: <br>If you do not have a Google Analytics account, go to the <a href=\"https://analytics.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google Analytics website</a> and sign up. After signing in, you will see the Google Analytics homepage. Click on the &#8216;Start<em> </em>measuring&#8217;<strong><em> </em></strong>button. This will lead you to the steps for configuring your Google Analytics account.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"695\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA-1-1024x695.png\" alt=\"Dashboard - how to add Google Analytics\n\" class=\"wp-image-11237\" style=\"object-fit:cover\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 53\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA-1-1024x695.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA-1-300x204.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA-1-768x521.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA-1-1536x1043.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA-1.png 1772w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 1 &#8211; Account creation</strong><br>In this step, you&#8217;ll need to provide an account name and choose different data-sharing options. You can set the account name same as your business name for convenience. Also choose options inside the Account Data Sharing Settings, to share the data that you collect in Google Analytics with Google.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"957\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA1-1-1024x957.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11238\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 54\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA1-1-1024x957.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA1-1-300x280.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA1-1-768x718.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA1-1-1536x1435.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA1-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 2 &#8211; Property Creation<br></strong>In this step, you will need to create an Analytics Property. Set the property name, select reporting time zone, and currency. Once you are done, click &#8216;Next&#8217; button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"552\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA2-1-1024x552.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11241\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 55\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA2-1-1024x552.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA2-1-300x162.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA2-1-768x414.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA2-1-1536x827.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA2-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 3 &#8211; Business details<br></strong>In this step, select an Industry category of your business, and then select a Business size. Once you are done, click on the &#8216;Next&#8217; button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"579\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1-1024x579.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11242\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 56\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1-1024x579.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1-300x170.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1-768x434.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1-1536x868.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1-400x226.png 400w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA3-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 4 &#8211; Business Objectives<br></strong>In this step, choose your business objectives for getting personalized reports of your business from Google Analytics. Select &#8216;Get baseline reports&#8217; option so that you get all reports of your business from Google Analytics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"665\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA4-1-1024x665.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11243\" style=\"width:840px;height:auto\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 57\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA4-1-1024x665.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA4-1-300x195.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA4-1-768x499.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA4-1-1536x997.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA4-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After making your selections, click on the<strong> </strong>&#8216;Create&#8217; button. A pop-up message appears with the<strong> Google Analytics Terms of Service Agreement</strong>. Accept the terms and conditions and click the &#8216;I Accept&#8217; button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"475\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA5-1-1024x475.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11244\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 58\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA5-1-1024x475.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA5-1-300x139.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA5-1-768x356.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA5-1-1536x712.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA5-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 5 &#8211; Data Collection<br></strong>In this step, we&#8217;ll choose a platform from which Google Analytics will collect data from. Since we are adding Google Analytics on our WordPress website, we&#8217;ll select Web as a platform.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"468\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA6-1-1024x468.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11245\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 59\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA6-1-1024x468.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA6-1-300x137.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA6-1-768x351.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA6-1-1536x702.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA6-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, set your website&#8217;s URL and a Stream name.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By default, Google Analytics enables the Enhanced Measurement option. This allows Google Analytics to track on-page elements and user interactions on those on-page elements such as Page views, Scrolls, Outbound clicks. etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on &#8216;Create stream&#8217; button once you are done.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"501\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA7-1-1-1024x501.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11247\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 60\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA7-1-1-1024x501.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA7-1-1-300x147.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA7-1-1-768x376.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA7-1-1-1536x752.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA7-1-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you will see the Web stream details screen, which indicates the successful creation of the web stream, but data collection is not active and prompts you to use Google Tag Manager.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Web stream details you can see your Stream details: Stream name, id, URL and Measurement or Tag ID. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1009\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA8-1-1024x1009.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11249\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 61\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA8-1-1024x1009.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA8-1-300x296.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA8-1-768x757.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA8-1.png 1487w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p>If you click on the View tag instructions button in the alert notice, methods and instructions on how to add Google Analytics to WordPress website will be shown.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We will not be going through <em><strong>Install with a website builder or CMS</strong></em> method and instructions. But you can try this method and follow the instructions to add Google Analytics in your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"779\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA9-1-1024x779.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11253\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 62\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA9-1-1024x779.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA9-1-300x228.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA9-1-768x584.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA9-1-1536x1168.png 1536w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/GA9-1.png 1782w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In this turorial, we will be more focused on installing Google Analytics in our WordPress website with &#8216;Install manually&#8217; method.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you switch to the <strong><em>Install manually</em></strong> method tab, you will see the Google Analytics tracking code.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"609\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ManualInstruction-1-1-1024x609.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11257\" title=\"How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024? 63\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ManualInstruction-1-1-1024x609.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ManualInstruction-1-1-300x179.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ManualInstruction-1-1-768x457.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ManualInstruction-1-1.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We will copy this Google Analytics tracking code as we will be using this tracking code to add Google Analytics to WordPress website using Method 1 below.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"2-add-google-analytics-to-word-press-website\"><strong>2.  Add Google Analytics to WordPress Website</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several methods to add Google Analytics to WordPress website. We will show you two simple methods below:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Method 1 &#8211; Adding code in the theme header.php file</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This method is for you if you prefer not to use a plugin. You can manually add the tracking code to your theme header template file.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Go to your WordPress dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Navigate to <em>Appearance > Theme File Editor</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Locate and click on the <em>header.php</em> file under Theme Files.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the tracking code from <em>Step &#8211; 5, Install manually</em>, before the closing <code>&lt;/head></code> tag.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Save the changes.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you are regularly updating your theme, then this method is unsuitable as all the changes to theme template files will be lost once you update the theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Method 2 &#8211; Using a Plugin</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the easiest method to add Google Analytics to WordPress website. You can add Google Analytics on your WordPress website using the plugins such as:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-analytics-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google Analytics for WordPress</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-site-kit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Site Kit by Google</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-analytify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Analytify</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ga-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GA Google Analytics</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/beehive-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Beehive Analytics</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li>and many more.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The main benefit of using above listed plugins is that you can see your Google Analytics reports on your WordPress dashboard without the need to visit your Google Analytics account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here, we have used MonsterInsights plugin for an example. MonsterInsights is one the popular Google Analytics plugins for WordPress and has over 3 million active WordPress installations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Add Google Analytics in WordPress using MonsterInsights plugin</strong>:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Go to your WordPress dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Navigate to <em>Plugins > Add New</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Search for &#8220;MonsterInsights&#8221; and once found, install &amp; activate it.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Follow the setup wizard to connect your Google Analytics account.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>It is this simple and easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"3-verify-the-installation\">3. Verify the Installation</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have added Google Analytics on your WordPress website using either of the two methods above, go to your Google Analytics account and check data is being receiving from your WordPress website and Google Analytics is providing you the real-time report.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"conclusion\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article has helped you add Google Analytics to your WordPress site. With the methods and instructions provided, we hope you can easily add Google Analytics to WordPress website and start collecting data to optimize your content, enhance user experience, and improve your marketing strategies. Whether you are new to this or an experienced site owner, integrating Google Analytics is essential for reaching your website goals and maximizing its potential.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You might be interested in creating successful email marketing campaigns, check out our article on <a href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/effective-email-marketing-strategies/\">Effective Email Marketing Strategies</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you find the article helpful, please share your experiences in the comment section below.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you for reading till the end.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-wordpress/\">How to add Google Analytics to your WordPress website easily in 2024?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress website in an easy way?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 03 Jun 2024 12:25:04 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WordPress Tutorial\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/?p=11201\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:390:\"<p>Securing your website is one of the crucial aspects of preventing malicious attacks and protecting...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-wordpress/\">How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress website in an easy way?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Themebeez Author\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14473:\"\n<p>Securing your website is one of the crucial aspects of preventing malicious attacks and protecting sensitive information. One of the fundamental steps to ensure your WordPress site is secure is by adding an SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) certificate.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An SSL certificate encrypts the data transmitted between your server and user browsers, protecting sensitive information such as login details and personal data. Additionally, having an SSL certificate can improve your search engine rankings, as Google prioritizes secure websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this blog post, you will discover how to install an SSL certificate on your WordPress website.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><h2>Table of Contents</h2><nav><ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-an-ssl\">What is an SSL?</a></li><li><a href=\"#what-is-an-ssl-certificate\">What is an SSL certificate?</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-does-an-ssl-certificate-works\">How does an SSL certificate works?</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-word-press\">How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress?</a></li><li><a href=\"#step-by-step-guide-to-installing-an-ssl-certificate-using-a-word-press-plugin\">Step-by-Step guide to installing an SSL certificate using a WordPress plugin</a><ul><li><a href=\"#step-1-install-and-activate-the-really-simple-ssl-plugin\">Step 1: Install and activate the Really Simple SSL plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#step-2-configure-the-plugin\">Step 2: Configure the plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#step-3-additional-configuration\">Step 3: Additional configuration</a></li><li><a href=\"#step-4-test-your-site\">Step 4: Test your site</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#enabling-ssl-on-word-press\">Enabling SSL on WordPress</a></li><li><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion</a></li></ul></nav></div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-an-ssl\">What is an SSL?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>SSL ( Secure Socket Layer) is an encryption protocol that encrypts the information exchanged between a web server and a web browser. It ensures the shared data remains safe and secure, providing a layer of security.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SSL is essential for various reasons :&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Protecting Sensitive Information</strong>: SSL is crucial for protecting sensitive data such as credit card numbers, login credentials, and personal information from cybercriminals.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Building User Trust</strong>: When users see the padlock icon and &#8220;https://&#8221; in the browser address bar, they know their connection is secure, which builds trust.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Preventing Cyber Attacks</strong>: SSL helps prevent various cyber threats, including man-in-the-middle attacks, where an attacker intercepts data between the user and the server.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-an-ssl-certificate\">What is an SSL certificate?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An SSL certificate is a digital certificate that verifies the website&#8217;s identity. It ensures that data passed between the web server and browsers remains private.&nbsp;SSL certificate serves various purposes such as security, SEO benefits, increased trust and credibility, compliance, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are 3 different types of SSL certificates:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Domain Validated(DV) certificates &#8211; These are the most basic types of certificates, verifying only the domain name.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Organization Validated(OV) certificates &#8211; These provide a higher level of security by verifying the organization’s identity.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Extended Validation (EV) certificates &#8211; These certificates offer the highest level of security, requiring a thorough vetting process of the organization and enabling the green address bar in browsers.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"how-does-an-ssl-certificate-works\">How does an SSL certificate works?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An SSL certificate ensures that data transferred between users and websites remains safe and secure. It uses an encryption algorithm and encrypts the data with keys so that attackers cannot read it in between. It uses the SSL/TSL Handshake protocol to create secure communication and safeguard data that may be sensitive information such as personally identifiable information(PIA), login credentials, financial information &amp; credit card numbers, and so on.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is a breakdown of how it works:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Establishing a secure connection</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Browser Connection:</strong> When users navigate to an SSL-secured website, their browser attempts to connect to the web server.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Server Identification:</strong> The server responds by sending a copy of its SSL certificate to the user&#8217;s browser.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"2\">\n<li><strong>Certificate Validation</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The browser verifies the SSL certificate to ensure it is from a trusted Certificate Authority (CA) and is not expired, revoked, or invalid. Once the certificate is validated, the browser informs the web server, sending a signed acknowledgment to initiate an SSL-encrypted session.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"3\">\n<li><strong>Session Key Generation</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Public Key Encryption:</strong> Once the certificate is validated, the browser generates a session key (a unique symmetric key for the session) and encrypts it using the server public key from the SSL certificate.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"4\">\n<li><strong>Establishing an Encrypted Session</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Session Key Exchange:</strong> The server decrypts the session key using its private key. Now, the browser and the server have the same session key to encrypt all further communication.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Secure Communication</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Data Encryption:</strong> With the session key established, all data transmitted between the browser and the server is encrypted, ensuring malicious attackers cannot intercept or tamper with sensitive information.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>By following this process, SSL ensures that data transferred between the server and the browser remains private and secure, protecting it from interception and tampering. This encryption helps to maintain data integrity and user trust, which is crucial for online transactions and secure communications.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-word-press\">How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you proceed, make sure to ascertain whether your website already has an SSL certificate or if it requires one.&nbsp; Most Web hosts provide free, paid, or third-party SSL certificates through <strong>Let’s Encrypt</strong>.  You can enable this directly from your hosting control panel. If your site does not have an SSL certificate or it is expired, you should install an SSL certificate or purchase from a Certificate Authority (CA).&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, you must create a backup of your entire site using the WordPress backup plugins.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Installing an SSL certificate on your WordPress site can be done in several ways. Here’s a simplified guide to the most common methods:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Plugin: Easiest method, ideal for non-technical users.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>cPanel: Directly manage SSL certificates via your hosting control panel.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Web Host/Server: Utilize your hosting provider’s tools or support for SSL installation, best for those with technical knowledge, offering complete control over the process.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step-by-step-guide-to-installing-an-ssl-certificate-using-a-word-press-plugin\">Step-by-Step guide to installing an SSL certificate using a WordPress plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ll guide you in installing the SSL certificate in a WordPress site using WordPress plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step-1-install-and-activate-the-really-simple-ssl-plugin\"><strong>Step 1: Install and activate the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/really-simple-ssl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Really Simple SSL</a> plugin</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. Log in to your WordPress dashboard:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Go to your WordPress admin panel.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Navigate to plugins:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"2\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In the left-hand menu, click <strong>Plugins&gt;&gt;Add New</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. Search for Really Simple SSL:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"3\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In the search bar, type<strong> Really Simple SSL.</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Locate the plugin in the search results,&nbsp; developed by Really Simple Plugins.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. Install and activate the plugin:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\" start=\"4\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click the <strong>Install Now </strong>button next to the Simple SSL plugin.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Once installed, click the <strong>Activate </strong>button.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step-2-configure-the-plugin\"><strong>Step 2: Configure the plugin</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. Activate SSL:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>After activation, the plugin will automatically redirect you to its setting page.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The plugin will automatically detect if your site has an active SSL certificate.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click on the <strong>Activate SSL </strong>button.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Update site URL to HTTPS:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The plugin will update your WordPress Address (URL) and Site Address (URL) to use HTTPS instead of HTTP.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step-3-additional-configuration\">Step 3: Additional configuration</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. Force SSL on all pages:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The plugin ensures all pages are loaded over HTTPS by setting up the necessary redirects.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2</strong>. <strong>Mixed content fixer:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Simple SSL includes a mixed content fixer that helps securely load all resources (images, scripts, stylesheets) over HTTPS.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. Check for issues:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Navigate to <strong>Settings&gt;&gt;SSL</strong> in your WordPress dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The plugin will alert you to any issues or mixed content that need addressing. Follow the recommended actions to resolve them.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"step-4-test-your-site\"><strong>Step 4: Test your site</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. Visit your site:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Open a new browser window and visit your website. Ensure the URL starts with <strong>https://</strong> and a padlock icon in the address bar indicating a secure connection.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Use online tools:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Tools like <a href=\"https://www.whynopadlock.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Why No Padlock?</a> or SSL Labs’ SSL Test can assist in confirming that your SSL certificate has been correctly configured and can identify any remaining mixed content issues.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"></ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"enabling-ssl-on-word-press\">Enabling SSL on WordPress</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>After successfully installing an SSL certificate, proceed to your WordPress dashboard and navigate to the <strong>Settings</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>From the Settings dropdown menu, click on General.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update your WordPress URLs.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"127\" src=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WordPress-URL-1-1024x127.png\" alt=\"Enabling SSL - How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress\n\" class=\"wp-image-11203\" title=\"How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress website in an easy way? 64\" srcset=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WordPress-URL-1-1024x127.png 1024w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WordPress-URL-1-300x37.png 300w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WordPress-URL-1-768x95.png 768w, https://themebeez.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WordPress-URL-1.png 1276w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click on the Save Changes button at the bottom. You’ll receive a confirmation message once the changes are applied. </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"conclusion\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article &nbsp;helped you to install an SSL certificate on your WordPress site. &nbsp;By adding an SSL certificate, you not only enhance your site&#8217;s security but also build trust with your visitors. However, remember that an SSL certificate is the first step toward website security. To fully protect your site, consider installing security plugins and following best practices for WordPress security.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For detailed guidance on securing your site, check out our article on the <a href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/best-wordpress-security-plugins/\"><strong>Best WordPress Security Plugins</strong></a><strong> </strong>and <a href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/wordpress-security/\"><strong>Tips To Improve WordPress Security</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p> If you found this article helpful or have any feedback, please share your experiences in the comment section below.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thank you for reading until the end!</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-wordpress/\">How to install an SSL certificate on WordPress website in an easy way?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://themebeez.com/blog\">Themebeez Blog</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/how-to-install-an-ssl-certificate-on-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:32:\"https://themebeez.com/blog/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"\n	1	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:48:\"WpOrg\\Requests\\Utility\\CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:19:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Fri, 04 Apr 2025 04:18:28 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:14:\"content-length\";s:5:\"49991\";s:6:\"cf-ray\";s:20:\"92ae007e1a774006-SIN\";s:6:\"server\";s:10:\"cloudflare\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"f08c4b5e902829da8df3c0216aeea6aa\"\";s:22:\"x-dns-prefetch-control\";s:2:\"on\";s:4:\"link\";s:63:\"<https://themebeez.com/blog/